## Debt to Equity Ratio
This measures the company's financial leverage.
- Total Liabilities = $3,054,996.05 (Total Current Liabilities)
- Total Equity = $11,824,937.81 (Total Owner's Equity)
- Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Equity = $3,054,996.05 / $11,824,937.81 = 0.258

## Net Profit Margin
This shows the percentage of revenue that turns into profit.
- Net Profit = -$1,175,062.19
- Total Revenue = $7,099,920.95
- Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100 = (-$1,175,062.19 / $7,099,920.95) × 100 = -16.55%

## Return on Assets (ROA)
This indicates how efficiently the company is using its assets to generate earnings.
- Net Profit = -$1,175,062.19
- Total Assets = $14,879,933.86
- ROA = (Net Profit / Total Assets) × 100 = (-$1,175,062.19 / $14,879,933.86) × 100 = -7.90%

## Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio
This measures how effectively a company is collecting its receivables.
- Total Revenue = $7,099,920.95
- Average Accounts Receivable = ($0 + $3,558,301.64) / 2 = $1,779,150.82
- Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Accounts Receivable = $7,099,920.95 / $1,779,150.82 = 3.99
